# Go build artifacts.
# IMPORTANT: bin/ is intentionally NOT ignored — bin/myserver.js is the
# npm wrapper that ships in the published package (per package.json
# `bin` mapping). Go binaries are built to the repo root (gitignored via
# `/myserver` below) or to dist/ via goreleaser; nothing in this repo
# legitimately writes to bin/. If someone accidentally `go build -o bin/`,
# git status will warn them rather than silently swallowing the binary.
dist/
*.exe
*.test
*.out
coverage.html

# Editor + OS noise
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# npm publishing artifacts
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*

# Local credentials never belong in source
.env
.env.local
credentials.json
/myserver
